Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.34,0:00:06.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(366,469)}Are you crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.88,0:00:10.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a letter from my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.80,0:00:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My best friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.47,0:00:16.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I was fifteen years old...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.35,0:00:19.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we tried to cross the Czech border together.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.94,0:00:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She was caught and sent back to Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.73,0:00:27.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She said she's doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.19,0:00:32.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She knows me better than anyone in my family...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.45,0:00:33.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A true friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.95,0:00:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows what kind of censorship\Nthis letter had to go through...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.74,0:00:40.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,before she could send it to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.58,0:00:44.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"If we ever get a chance to meet again..."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.21,0:00:46.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"please come to this place... "{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.63,0:00:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"Cedok Bridge, the Three Frogs."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.76,0:00:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to go back... to Prague...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.31,0:00:58.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Margot...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.69,0:01:06.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.86,0:01:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.20,0:01:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please call me by my real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.70,0:01:18.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just for tonight, I'd like you to use my real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.33,0:01:22.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Helenka Novakowa.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.75,0:01:29.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just for tonight, I'm not Margot Langer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.48,0:03:02.47,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(399,0)\pos(364,354)}The Monster's Love Letter
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.76,0:03:02.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sold my Reiser-Berger Pharmaceutical\Nstock in the nick of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.26,0:03:06.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I bought some Kneuter Research stock...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.68,0:03:07.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and I hit the jackpot.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.47,0:03:12.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just had to celebrate after that...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.35,0:03:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you drink?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.73,0:03:15.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.73,0:03:18.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm appalled.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.36,0:03:20.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was just one glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.11,0:03:21.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've said this many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.24,0:03:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you're an alcoholic...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.61,0:03:27.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it doesn't matter how much you drink, it's all the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.78,0:03:32.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you've been ditching the alcohol\Nrehab group I recommended for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.21,0:03:33.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.83,0:03:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doc, can you keep this secret?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.71,0:03:41.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The thing is, there's a woman I want you to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.55,0:03:44.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Another one of your lovers?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.55,0:03:45.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.22,0:03:49.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's a really bad alcoholic.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.18,0:03:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's waiting right outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.47,0:03:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you take a quick look at her?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.85,0:03:54.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that without an appointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.73,0:03:56.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have one set up for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.90,0:04:00.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A quick look would be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.07,0:04:02.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got a house call to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.28,0:04:03.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For a very important patient, at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.78,0:04:07.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I went to Prague, in the Czech Republic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.82,0:04:10.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.79,0:04:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prague Castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.70,0:04:14.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The cathedrals, with their marvelous Gothic architecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.75,0:04:18.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The view of the old commercial district\Nat night was also stunning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.79,0:04:22.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was like I was in a fairyland.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.01,0:04:23.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Cedok Bridge...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.92,0:04:26.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you go to Ceddk Bridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.76,0:04:30.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, just as you asked me to.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.14,0:04:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.77,0:04:35.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I found it! The Three Frogs!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.73,0:04:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was the woman there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.11,0:04:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.98,0:04:43.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.11,0:04:45.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To be honest...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.36,0:04:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't find anything by going there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.95,0:04:52.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tenma, Nina, and even Dieter...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.66,0:04:54.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't find anything that indicates where they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.54,0:05:01.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.84,0:05:07.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a rabbit's foot that brings good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.51,0:05:12.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's for our child you're carrying...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.77,0:05:19.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Margot... no, Helenka...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.27,0:05:19.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.45,0:05:28.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.23,0:05:38.69,Location,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(359,316)}Prague
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.02,0:05:56.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.02,0:05:57.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.43,0:06:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've come from Germany, and I'm\Ntrying to find a missing woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.07,0:06:04.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know her?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.78,0:06:06.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Margot Langer...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.23,0:06:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, I mean Helenka Novakowa.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.99,0:06:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Helenka...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.08,0:06:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Mr. Schuwald...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.50,0:06:19.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your son, Karl, mentioned this to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.50,0:06:23.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You haven't been eating again, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.96,0:06:30.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that during the fire in the\NUniversity of Munich Library...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.26,0:06:33.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you experienced something truly terrifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.60,0:06:38.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I understand that you haven't overcome that fear yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.85,0:06:41.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you still have Karl...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.40,0:06:46.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who is such a splendid son.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.99,0:06:50.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need to worry anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.24,0:06:53.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just eat properly!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.16,0:06:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That monster...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.41,0:07:00.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as that monster exists, I will...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.29,0:07:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did that monster know so\Nmuch about Margot Langer?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.13,0:07:15.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He knew more than my son did.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.31,0:07:22.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,\NMargot had a friend in Prague who knew\Nher better than her own family did.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.85,0:07:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The woman she exchanged letters with.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.81,0:07:27.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Around 1980...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.11,0:07:30.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you went searching for the missing Margot...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.03,0:07:34.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and you met that woman in Prague.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.99,0:07:36.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.28,0:07:42.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought she may have heard something from Margot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.41,0:07:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.25,0:07:47.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She hadn't heard anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.21,0:07:51.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We talked about Margot for a little while in her doorway.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.84,0:07:54.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.59,0:07:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they were listening...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.64,0:07:58.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to our conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.10,0:07:59.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.64,0:08:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were quietly listening...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.64,0:08:06.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,standing behind the woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.48,0:08:08.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were twins...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.74,0:08:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.70,0:08:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a seat over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.78,0:08:20.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were referred by Mr. Talbach.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.70,0:08:24.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You also have drinking problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.46,0:08:27.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's just have a casual conversation for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.50,0:08:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.46,0:08:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Mehres?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.75,0:08:32.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in the middle of a counseling session.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.17,0:08:33.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just now, on TV...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.76,0:08:35.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tenma! Dr. Tenma...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.59,0:08:38.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me for a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.18,0:08:40.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I repeat...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.72,0:08:41.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Czech police have just announced...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.81,0:08:43.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the capture of the main suspect in the poisoning...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.81,0:08:48.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}of three murdered doctors from Eisler Memorial\NHospital in D{\fnMeiryo U}ü{\fnNarkisim}sseldorf, Germany...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.44,0:08:52.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the murders of the journalist Mauler\Nand the Fortners in Heidelberg...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.90,0:08:55.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and the street murder at Heidelberg Castle.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.45,0:08:59.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Japanese doctor, Kenzou Tenma,\Nwho had been hiding in Prague...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.41,0:09:02.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}was apprehended on the afternoon of the 5th.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.87,0:09:05.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We're still waiting for more information\Non the details of his arrest...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.29,0:09:11.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}which will be released during\Nthe police press conference.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.83,0:09:10.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.96,0:09:12.11,Default 2,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't come in here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.13,0:09:13.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a private office...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.71,0:09:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so please wait in the other room, Ms. Eva Heinemann!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.76,0:09:20.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kenzou...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.51,0:09:23.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I'm late, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.47,0:09:27.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hess, you look ten years younger.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.85,0:09:30.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe because I've been taking\Ncare of my grandkids too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.90,0:09:32.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How've you been, Hubert?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.86,0:09:36.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I somehow made it to my senior year...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.86,0:09:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Kiefer, I heard you've been doing very well lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.82,0:09:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been bragging that I know a script writer\Nwho's been invited to Hollywood.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.66,0:09:44.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so honored...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.00,0:09:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I just happened to catch a producer's eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.63,0:09:50.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My mind's become very sharp...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.88,0:09:54.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and new ideas just keep pouring into my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.00,0:09:55.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's great to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.97,0:09:59.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since that surgery...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.18,0:10:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that brain surgery hadn't been successful...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.27,0:10:06.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,right now, I'd be...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.94,0:10:13.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't have been able to take walks\Nin the park with my grandchildren.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.57,0:10:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That seat...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.49,0:10:19.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was always drinking tea by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.49,0:10:23.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though there were other cafes where doctors met...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.45,0:10:27.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he always came to this one, in the\Nback of Eisler Memorial Hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.83,0:10:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When we the patients, would come here...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.75,0:10:33.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he would look up from over there...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.17,0:10:36.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and wave at us with a smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.51,0:10:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a kind doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.38,0:10:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.88,0:10:44.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way a kind doctor like\Nhim could do something like this
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.31,0:10:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the reason I asked you to come today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.56,0:10:52.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, even the people who couldn't make it here\Ntoday must be feeling the same way...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.60,0:10:56.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if they were Dr. Tenma's former patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.36,0:10:59.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Schumann, we've got trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.70,0:11:01.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old man Merkel collapsed!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.16,0:11:04.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I'll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.91,0:11:06.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in the middle of something right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.87,0:11:08.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but please wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.70,0:11:10.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.71,0:11:14.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma wouldn't have done such a thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.79,0:11:17.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down and listen, Mom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.09,0:11:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, go to him, honey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.55,0:11:21.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but Petra...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.72,0:11:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There s no "but"!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.76,0:11:26.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma's been arrested for crimes he didn't commit!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.93,0:11:30.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If not for him, I wouldn't be here right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.19,0:11:37.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to pretend nothing happened,\Nwhen your wife's savior is in big trouble?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.07,0:11:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about the village?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.82,0:11:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.86,0:11:44.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In this village, I'm the only doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.95,0:11:48.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I leave, what's going to happen\Nto the people in this village?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.16,0:11:50.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make excuses!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.83,0:11:52.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want to go, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.16,0:11:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry and go save Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.21,0:11:58.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When a doctor has patients, he cannot leave them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.63,0:12:02.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma would do the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.38,0:12:05.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor, please hurry and see me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.89,0:12:08.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm prepping right now, so wait there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.22,0:12:09.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How long are you gonna make us wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.93,0:12:11.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't complain!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.48,0:12:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's been going to medical school recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.19,0:12:17.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She still runs an unauthorized clinic for us at her own risk!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.36,0:12:26.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you stay in the darkness, you'll sink into the darkness...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.03,0:12:28.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Shine light upon it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.33,0:12:29.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm sure, you can become a doctor.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.74,0:12:34.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm sure you'll be a good doctor.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.71,0:12:36.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.88,0:12:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, let's begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.05,0:12:49.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First patient, please come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.60,0:12:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get a lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.02,0:12:52.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.18,0:12:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But we still don't know where in Germany\NTenma will be transferred.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.06,0:13:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pick a lawyer for each state...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.70,0:13:07.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The best criminal lawyers out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.95,0:13:08.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.91,0:13:10.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only that man...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.70,0:13:14.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel only that man can do it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.12,0:13:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only he can obliterate the monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.46,0:13:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For now, let's gather more people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.75,0:13:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's call out to Dr. Tenma's former patients.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.30,0:13:31.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alone, each of us may not have much \N influence, but if we all pull together...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.64,0:13:32.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.10,0:13:36.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's ask Eisler Memorial for their cooperation...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.85,0:13:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and create a rescue association...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.19,0:13:39.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.56,0:13:44.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eisler Memorial won't help with that kind of thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.28,0:13:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been listening to you for a little while now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.57,0:13:50.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a tearjerker!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.07,0:13:54.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.04,0:13:58.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are you guys going to prove Tenma's innocence?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.87,0:14:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Becker!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.92,0:14:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He had a motive, and no alibi at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.51,0:14:09.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard they also found material evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.80,0:14:17.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you get together and make a\Nfuss, or hire a competent lawyer...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.35,0:14:23.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it s impossible to prove Tenma's innocence either way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.23,0:14:28.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's unfortunate, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.69,0:14:30.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such an eminent doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.49,0:14:34.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's unfortunate.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.79,0:14:38.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll ask you again, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.83,0:14:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what kind of relationship do you have with Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.80,0:14:47.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Eva Heinemann.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.42,0:14:49.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know who you are, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.13,0:14:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to rescue Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.55,0:14:57.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're tagging along out of curiosity,\NI'd prefer you didn't come.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.68,0:14:58.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eva...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.98,0:15:00.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heinemann...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.44,0:15:02.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heinemann?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.06,0:15:04.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heinemann...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.23,0:15:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could if be that you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.19,0:15:12.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,related to Director Heinemann, who was\Nmurdered at Eisler Memorial Hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.61,0:15:14.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Tenma...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.57,0:15:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is the man who ruined my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.83,0:15:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.08,0:15:24.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the only one who can save him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.71,0:15:27.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.00,0:15:29.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saw what?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.99,0:15:38.66,Name,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(267,0)\pos(321,383)}St. Jaromir Hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.51,0:15:39.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kenzou Tenma, who has been taken \Ninto custody in Prague...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.64,0:15:44.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}will be deported to Germany within\Nthe next couple of days to stand trial.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.73,0:15:49.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He will be transferred to D{\fnMeiryo U}ü{\fnNarkisim}sseldorff\Nwhere the string of murders began.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.44,0:15:50.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}After an interrogation...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.94,0:15:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the police are going to inspect\Nthe crime scene with Dr. Tenma.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.49,0:15:52.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.95,0:15:54.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.91,0:15:56.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That man...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.20,0:15:57.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.83,0:15:59.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.37,0:16:02.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Suk, he's the man who saved your life.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.87,0:16:05.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's because of his emergency treatment that you're alive.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.50,0:16:09.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Dr. Tenma is also being accused\N\Nor crimes he did not commit.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.71,0:16:13.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's in the same situation as you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.55,0:16:15.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The man who saved my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.43,0:16:17.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he's also in the same situation as me...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.80,0:16:19.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You're a detective, aren't you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.06,0:16:21.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you're a detective...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.39,0:16:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}then you have to calmly dissect the situation.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.52,0:16:28.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you don't want to be betrayed anymore...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.44,0:16:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}then start doubting the person\Nyou want to doubt the least{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.37,0:16:42.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to go...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.87,0:16:45.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Somehow, I have to get to Prague Station...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.29,0:16:48.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and talk with Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.38,0:16:54.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've been looking for you, Suk.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.84,0:16:56.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Blazek...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.43,0:16:58.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Stransky...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.51,0:16:59.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.47,0:17:01.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to run anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.51,0:17:02.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.56,0:17:04.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've put you through quite a bit of trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.39,0:17:06.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've been cleared of all charges.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.81,0:17:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A letter was delivered to the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.15,0:17:12.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.28,0:17:14.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A letter...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.49,0:17:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a confession with the kinds of details...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.32,0:17:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,regarding the whole case that\Nonly the killer would know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.91,0:17:22.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All the charges against you have been dropped.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.16,0:17:23.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who sent the letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.37,0:17:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone by the name of Grimmer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.54,0:17:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.87,0:17:32.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've already put a warrant out for\NGrimmer as the prime suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.05,0:17:34.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.13,0:17:37.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay now, Suk.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.63,0:17:41.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Zeman's murder, the\Ncommissioner's poisoning...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.97,0:17:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the special task force murders...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.14,0:17:47.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,have now all been resolved.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.79,0:18:56.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Where have you been, Lunge?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.80,0:18:58.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I've been calling your number all day!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.80,0:19:00.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.22,0:19:01.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I went out sightseeing for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.59,0:19:04.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Geez! Stop playing dumb!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.47,0:19:05.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Playing dumb?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.85,0:19:07.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.22,0:19:08.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Knock it off already!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.56,0:19:10.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I bet you've heard the news!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.19,0:19:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.40,0:19:14.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About Dr. Tenma's arrest, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.73,0:19:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Congratulations, Lunge.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.69,0:19:17.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.53,0:19:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You knew, right?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.15,0:19:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That Tenma was hiding out in Prague.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.03,0:19:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Good job Lunge.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.99,0:19:27.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is the result of your thorough investigation.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.79,0:19:33.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}We contacted the Czech police immediately and\Ncompleted the deportation arrangements.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.87,0:19:37.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Tenma will be transferred to D{\fnMeiryo U}ü{\fnNarkisim}sseldorf\Ntomorrow afternoon.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.34,0:19:39.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Since you're in charge of this case...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.17,0:19:42.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want you to personally supervise his transfer.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.97,0:19:45.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Anyway, you did a good job, Lunge.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.05,0:19:46.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Congratulations.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.47,0:19:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you assign it to someone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.02,0:19:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Huh?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.18,0:19:52.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prague is a nice place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.02,0:19:53.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.35,0:19:55.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.48,0:19:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still on vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.77,0:19:58.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hey, Lunge!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.69,0:20:00.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What are you saying?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.03,0:20:00.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hey!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.86,0:20:04.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please let me see Dr. Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.66,0:20:08.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been telling you, you can't see him
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.12,0:20:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.45,0:20:11.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't this country become a democracy
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.00,0:20:15.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tenma is about to be deported back to Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.58,0:20:18.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before that happens, even if only for a little...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.25,0:20:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we wasted our time.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.46,0:20:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though we came all the way to Prague...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.05,0:20:23.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.88,0:20:25.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even just a quick look!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.85,0:20:28.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.14,0:20:33.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This way, come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.32,0:20:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When we interrogate someone...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.12,0:20:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what kind of person do you think\Nis the toughest to crack?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.29,0:20:55.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone whose expression never changes.\Nregardless of the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.92,0:20:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone who doesn't say a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.09,0:21:03.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That kind of person.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.56,0:21:16.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A love letter from a monster to a beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.85,0:21:19.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like the draft for a novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.11,0:21:24.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"I've been watching you all this time."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.61,0:21:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"To eat up every bit of you."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.03,0:21:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"But instead, everything about you has devoured me."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.16,0:21:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"I wonder what I look like to you,\Nwho is collapsing into ruin."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.04,0:21:42.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"That which you left me, which is collapsing into ruin."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.67,0:21:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"You left me with such beautiful jewels."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.42,0:21:49.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"The twins, who are like eternal life itself."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.76,0:21:52.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"The greatest sin..."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.64,0:21:54.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"is to take away a person's name."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.43,0:21:57.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"Reclaim your name."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.69,0:21:59.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"I return your name to you."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.65,0:22:02.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"Your name is... Anna."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.40,0:22:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"I'm filled with sorrow now."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.36,0:22:07.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"Filled with sorrow..."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.61,0:22:09.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"Filled with sorrow..."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.70,0:22:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Filled with sorrow..."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.45,0:22:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It exists...!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.54,0:22:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The many people who died in that room...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.79,0:22:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.63,0:22:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A terrifying monster was born!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.88,0:22:31.05,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(170,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.05,0:22:44.48,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,475)}Cherish what you know is true in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.05,0:22:44.48,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(201,21)}Ima kono sekai de wakaru koto mitsumete
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.48,0:22:47.44,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(182,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.44,0:23:01.12,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(198,472)}Please believe in the kindness of your eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.44,0:23:01.12,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,21)}Anata no hitomi no yasashisa wo shinjite
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.72,0:23:25.98,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(196,473)}Make it home to your land of harmony
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.98,0:23:34.40,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(195,473)}Make it home to your land of purity
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.40,0:23:36.86,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,246)\pos(187,472)}Make it home
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.70,0:22:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
